(43, 3, 26, 44, 19, 26, 27, 'all men come to him', 'Influence of Preachers on Followers', 'This connection highlights the theme of influential figures drawing followers to themselves. In John, Jesus is gaining followers, while in Acts, Paul is persuading many away from idol worship.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 26, 46, 3, 3, 5, 'all men come to him', 'Carnality and Division in Ministry', 'This connection highlights the theme of division among followers in both passages. John 3:26 mentions people coming to Jesus, while 1 Corinthians 3:3-5 addresses divisions among those claiming allegiance to different leaders.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
